⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Hister
node N1 · N1 · ⟦Hister:N1:87d1ab⟧

WHO   — Hister — the word read as a man
WHAT  — The most famous of the seer's cryptic words — a place-name in the verse that twentieth-century readers retrofitted onto Adolf Hitler; a textbook case of how the quatrains' ambiguity invites projection.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a single ambiguous word, left obscure, can be bent to any age that reads it; because the resemblance of Hister to Hitler was too tempting to leave alone; because a prophecy that names a river can be made, after the fact, to name a tyrant.
HOW   — By the slippage between Latin geography and modern hindsight — Hister the Danube becoming "Hister" the man; by reading the verse backward from a known event and calling the fit a foretelling.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was a river's name in an old book — and an age in need of an omen made me a monster.

